<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="403" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KAC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the President’s
                                    Special Assistant</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d403fn1">Sent via Army channels.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-01">December 1, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>For immediate delivery to <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Harry
                                    Hopkins</persName> visiting party from <persName corresp="#p_KAC1">Kirk</persName>. I have received an urgent but
                                garbled message from <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">Steinhardt</persName> at Ankara from which I gather that he
                                wishes me to inform you that neither he nor the British Ambassador
                                at Ankara<note n="2" xml:id="d403fn2"><persName corresp="#p_KHSH1">Sir Hughe Knatchbull-Hugessen</persName>.</note> has
                                received any message from your party and that he believes that
                                communications from Tehran may be temporarily suspended.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>